channel.title: Compiler help (MAC)
channel.description:
Hello i need help with a small compiler problem i have.
when i compile using the terminal the "cd" space then i write "javac *.java" and it compiles perfectly in the terminal and some folders compile such as announcements but others such as objectmanager.java or anything in the src does not get compiled and does not get changed in the game itself.
if u can help pls post.
"note: some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. note: recompile with -xlint:unchecked for details press any key to continue . . ."
this is what i get but that cannot be correct because i erased everything in the objectmanager and left it blank but still i get that nothing is wrong

item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

That’s just a notification that some of the methods that are used in the program are outdated, and could potentially cause problems. However, if this is a normal 317 client, you can ignore it.

item.title: Compiler help (MAC)
item.dc:creator: @Pixore Pixore
item.description:
@Pixore wrote:

Well I don’t very well understand the answer, but try compiling again than shut the server off turn it back on and try again, seems like the only logical thing, because a compiler is not supposed to compile a part of a folder, it’s supposed to do the whole thing.
